before you went off to practice.

02:38.780 --> 02:39.599
Oh.

02:41.280 --> 02:42.190
Why?

02:46.490 --> 02:47.946
[utensils clinking]

02:48.040 --> 02:51.077
That girl's mother made a statement
in the press, apparently.

02:51.880 --> 02:52.699
Yeah?

02:53.920 --> 02:55.581
You haven't been following it?

02:56.090 --> 02:58.376
Uh, Dad and Warren told me
to keep my head down,

02:58.460 --> 03:01.122
so, you know, that's what I've been doing.

03:04.550 --> 03:06.302
So school's been fine, then?

03:06.970 --> 03:08.517
With all this drama?

03:11.560 --> 03:13.516
Yeah, yeah. Everything's great.

03:15.110 --> 03:18.022
You know, just gearing up for the season.

03:22.360 --> 03:24.271
Let me know
if you need someone to talk to.

03:25.030 --> 03:26.770
Dr. Pierce would be glad to see you.

03:28.700 --> 03:30.076
Or your counselor at school.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.786
What's his name? Mr. Porter?

03:35.500 --> 03:37.081
No, thanks. I'm good, Mom. [scoffs]

03:39.840 --> 03:43.674
-All right, honey. Have a great day.
-Yeah, you, too.

03:44.180 --> 03:45.670
-Don't work too hard.
-Yeah.

03:47.430 --> 03:50.763
[Marcus] But the truth is,
privilege is a trap all its own.

03:53.140 --> 03:55.608
What the fuck? What are you doing here?

03:57.020 --> 03:59.978
